<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="80" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,258,1399]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1338,1363]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name of this species derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1098,1339,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Homaloxestis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciformis">
<emphasis box="[992,1098,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">aciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(acicular), in reference to the long acicular distal thorn of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
